==English==
'''Stop word''' is an expression very common in the information retrieval (i.e. search engines) and text mining field that is used to designate words, terms or expressions that are not important (i.e. irrelevant) to the process or that must be ignored. Usually the words that falls in this category are the ones with very high frequency such as prepositions (''a'', ''to'' etc.). 

In Google, for example, a search using the preposition ''a'' may return almost all elements indexed, since this word is very common. 

